# Emmanuel Goldstein · the enemy of the people

a character of 1984 — a member of the NOUTHESIA universe of warnings. emergence: spiritual. moniker ⟦Emmanuel Goldstein:1984:cfe354⟧

**who —** Emmanuel Goldstein — the Party's official traitor and arch-enemy, author of the forbidden Book.
**what —** The designated hate-object and the (perhaps Party-written) resistance: the focus of the Two Minutes Hate and the bait for would-be rebels.
**where —** In propaganda and in the pages O'Brien hands to Winston.
**why —** Because a regime defines itself by an enemy — and may invent both the enemy and the rebellion that opposes him.
**how —** By a face for the daily Hate and a Book that explains the system too perfectly to be safe.

**the seal —** I am the enemy the Party needs — and perhaps the Party wrote me, so that every rebel reads my Book on the way to Room 101.

